Overexposure, static, blurred details, subtitles, paintings, pictures, still, overall gray, worst quality, low quality, JPEG compression residue, ugly, mutilated, redundant fingers, poorly painted hands, poorly painted faces, deformed, disfigured, deformed limbs, fused fingers, cluttered background, three legs, a lot of people in the background, upside down
A whimsical video of a yellow rubber duck wearing a cowboy hat and rugged clothes, he floats in a foamy bubble bath, the waters are rough and there are waves as if the rubber duck is in a rough ocean
The yellow nodes are for removing the first 6 frames from the image, these are junk frames that hurt the natural flow of the video â†“

If your machine is capable, try switching the RED nodes. using the VAE Decode node will assist in removing color glitching. 
Simply connect the latent output from the KSampler (First Pass) to the samples input of the VAE decode node. 
Then, connect the image output from the VAE Decode node to the ImagePass node

This Extend Video part is HIGHLY EXPERIMENTAL and requires a strong GPU and lots of RAM. 
It will take the last frame of the video generated in the first pass and generate another video based on that last frame. 
It will then combine the videos for a longer video.
If you do not wish to extend the video, use my other I2V workflow.

If your machine is capable, try switching the RED nodes. using the VAE Decode node will assist in removing color glitching. 
Simply connect the latent output from the KSampler (Second Pass) node to the samples input of the VAE decode node. 
Then, connect the image output from the VAE Decode node to the ImagePass node

At the time of updating this workflow, Skip Layer Guidance doesn't work. 
Try to re enable it from time to time, might've been fixed.

Select the correct model_type for TeaCache to work! 
The unet_name in the Load Diffusion Model node should match the model_type in the TeaCache node.

Lower max_skip_steps if you're getting lack of motion or artifacts

I found that for TeaCache, higher shift and higher steps provide much better results, experiment as you wish.

SageAttention disabled by default, if you're systems supports that enable it. 
If you enabled it and wish to disable, you have to change sage_attention in the node to disabled and run your workflow again in order for it to disable

I recommend using the LSDIR upscaler, get it here: 
https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-LSDIR
